Supervisors: <a href="https://www.ar.tum.de/ai/lehrstuhl/mitarbeiter-alt/gerhard-schubert/">Gerhard Schubert</a>, <a href="https://www.ar.tum.de/ai/lehrstuhl/mitarbeiter/frank-petzold/">Frank Petzold</a></p>

<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gmxF8yq4pE56tA1L83YjcZ0Cnx8KCGCq/view?usp=sharing">Document</a></p>

<p>For the <a href="https://www.ar.tum.de/ai/lehre/master/wahlmodule/performance-based-design-wise-202021/">Performance Based Design</a> project, we develop a plugin in Rhino to help architects with the task Abstandsfl√§che. This plugin can compute the maximum building volume and the optimal numbers of bulding blocks based on the legal and physical restrictions defined by the user such as maximum height or GFZ. In addition, we consider the adaptation to the staircases.</p>

